HEADWORD: Claymore
<hw>Clay"more`</hw> <pr>(kl⟦amac⟧"m⟦omac⟧r`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gael. <ets>claidheamhmor</ets> a broadsword; Gael.
<ets>claidheamh</ets> sword + <ets>mor</ets> great, large. Cf.
<er>Glaymore</er>.]</ety> <def>A large two-handed sword used formerly by
the Scottish Highlanders.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

